                                                           Network Interface Card (NIC)
                                                           
•	A network interface card is a hardware component that connects a computer to a network.
•	It is responsible for transmitting and receiving data packets over a network.
•	a MAC (Media Access Control) address is linked to a NIC (Network Interface Card)
                                                                  
                                                                   
                                                                    Types of NIC:


1.Wired NIC
•	Wired NICs use a physical cable to connect to a network.
•	Such as an Ethernet cable.

2.Wireless NIC
•	Wireless NIC uses radio waves to connect to a network.
•	Such as Wi-Fi.

3.Virtual NIC
•	Virtual NICs are software-based NICs that provide a virtual network interface for virtual machines .

